org.apache.taverna.invocation

Class Event<EventType extends Event<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.taverna.invocation.Event<EventType>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDispatchEvent, IterationInternalEvent, WorkflowDataToken

    public abstract class Event<EventType extends Event<?>>
extends Object
    Abstract superclass of all 'event' types within a workflow invocation. These are the Job and Completion events which are used internally within a Processor, in particular by the dispatch stack and iteration system, and the WorkflowDataToken which is the only event class that can exist outside of a Processor boundary (and is therefore the most significant one for users of the API)
    Author:
    Tom Oinn

        public final boolean isFinal()

      • getOwningProcess

        public final String getOwningProcess()
        The event has an owner, this is represented as a String object but the ownership is hierarchical in nature. The String is a colon separated list of alphanumeric process identifiers, with identifiers being pushed onto this list on entry to a process and popped off on exit.
        Returns:
        String of colon separated process identifiers owning this Job

      • getContext

        public final InvocationContext getContext()

      • popOwningProcess

        public abstract EventType popOwningProcess()
                                    throws ProcessIdentifierException
        Return a copy of the event subclass with the last owning process removed from the owning process list. For example, if the event had owner 'foo:bar' this would return a duplicate event with owner 'foo'. If the owning process is the empty string this is invalid and will throw a ProcessIdentifierException
        Returns:
        a copy of the event with the parent process identifier
        Throws:
        ProcessIdentifierException

      • pushOwningProcess

        public abstract EventType pushOwningProcess(String localProcessName)
                                     throws ProcessIdentifierException
        Return a copy of the event subclass with the specified local process name appended to the owning process identifier field. If the original owner was 'foo' and this was called with 'bar' you'd end up with a copy of the subclass with owner 'foo:bar'
        Parameters:
        localProcessName - name to add
        Returns:
        the modified event
        Throws:
        ProcessIdentifierException - if the local process name contains the ':' character

      • getIndex

        public final int[] getIndex()
        Events have an index placing them in a conceptual tree structure. This index is carried along with the event and used at various points to drive iteration and ensure that separate jobs are kept that way

      • popOwner

        protected final String popOwner()
                         throws ProcessIdentifierException
        Helper method for implementations of popOwningProcess, this constructs the appropriate process identifier after the leaf has been removed and returns it. If there is no leaf to remove, i.e. the current process identifier is the empty string, then ProcessIdentifierException is thrown
        Returns:
        Throws:
        ProcessIdentifierException

      • pushOwner

        protected final String pushOwner(String newLocalProcess)
                          throws ProcessIdentifierException
        Helper method for implementations of pushOwningProcess, appends the specified local name to the current owning process identifier and returns the new id. This doesn't change the current process identifier. If there is a colon ':' in the specified name this is invalid and will throw ProcessIdentifierException at you.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        Throws:
